      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the process as requested:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09D_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `J09D`.\n2. Added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n3. Classified each house:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Applied overrides:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 500–599 → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1` between 900–999 → `EVU`\n   - Otherwise: `< 3` equipment numbers → `KSA`, else `EVU`.\n4. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` using `ANLAGE` ↔ `Installation`, bringing in `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined with `net_master` and `sales_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - Where both net and sales records exist, preferred the sales fields and ignored the net ones; kept net data only when no sales data existed.\n5. Exported the final dataset to `J09D.csv` with exactly these columns and order:  \n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n6. Emailed the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com` with a short cover message.\n7. Dropped the temporary table `J09D_temp`.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also output the SQL used for your documentation or reuse in other tours.",
